#math 
> [[3-21-22 Notes - Barycentric Coordinates|3-21-22 Notes - Barycentric Coordinates]]

A weighted sum of points whose weights add up to 1.
$$
\boxed{
\begin{align}
X = a\cdot A + b\cdot B \\
a + b = 1
\end{align}
}
$$

**This doesn't work for points that aren't on the line formed between the 2 points!**

Though we can also do this on a plane!: [[Barycentric Coordinates with 3 Points|Barycentric Coordinates with 3 Points]]

**Notation:**
$$
X = \left[\frac{1}{3},\frac{1}{2},\frac{1}{6}\right]
$$
Square brackets $[]$, and each element indicates $a$, $b$, or in this case (a [[Barycentric Coordinates with 3 Points|tri or plane]]) $c$.
Cartesian coordinates will be indicated with $()$
